        "author": "Sarah Rossi", 
        "content": "<div><p>I&#8217;d like to pose a question to John and the RISD community at large:<br/>\nWhat are everyone&#8217;s thoughts on students who do not meet academic expectations? (ie, consistently do not show up for classes, do not complete assignments, etc) and are still allowed enrollment at RISD.  Is it more important that a professor/department ignores problem students (and lets them complete their degree at RISD) so as to keep the number of students in the department up (looks good on paper), or is it more important that a professor/department have the integrity to dismiss the students from RISD?<br/>\nI know my answer, but I wonder if I am missing an integral view on the situation.<br/>\nThanks!\n</p><p/></div>", 
        "date": "Sun, 12 Oct 2008 21:05:00"
