        "author": "Alpkan Kirayoglu", 
        "content": "<div><p>I would like to bring up an issue about offered courses and registration.<br/>\nI have been experiencing some difficulties at registering for classes that I feel very important for my education. Most of the classes are only offered once a year, and limited to twelve students. As an example, the type design class (GRAPH-3859-01) gets filled in an hour every year, and even its wait-list is longer than twelve students. I think based on the demand, an alternative class (from the same or a different instructor) must be offered.<br/>\nI am very frustrated because I have been missing out all the courses that affected my decision on choosing RISD over other schools.</p>\n<p>Thank you.\n</p><p/></div>", 
