        "author": "Anne Prentnieks", 
        "content": "<div><p>I would like to propose a thread about on-campus parking.</p>\n<p>I live far off campus and have just received my fifth parking ticket since December (all on RISD campus), for parking on College Street during my three-hour class. Since these are from the City of Providence, and not public safety, each ticket is $100. I am Broke. From what I can tell, there are no students lots on campus, or at least centrally-located lots. Also, it is apparently illegal to park on most streets within the vicinity without a permit. Is there a permit system in place for students? If not, perhaps RISD can look into securing parking space for students, or issuing permits.<br/>\nAlternately, perhaps RISD can pay my parking tickets? (kidding&#8230; sort of)<br/>\nThank you!\n</p><p/></div>", 
