        "author": "Marta Bustillo", 
        "content": "<div><p>I would like to start a new thread about a new screening series that FAV and the Library are collaborating on. The series is called 228 at Eight, and it will take place every Thursday evening at 8 pm, in room 228 of the RISD Library. We will be screening documentaries and avant-garde films from the RISD Library collection, together with anything else that anyone else wants to bring. Think open mic=open screening. DVD, VHS and .MOVs are the only formats we can show at present. Sign up at <a href=\"mailto:dhlynsky@risd.edu\">dhlynsky@risd.edu</a> for organization&#8217;s sake.</p>\n<p>Next week we will be screening &#8220;Al Otro Lado&#8221;, a documentary by RISD alumna Natalia Almada. Here is a description of the film and a link to the director&#8217;s website:</p>\n<p>&#8220;An aspiring corrido composer from the drug capital of Mexico faces two choices to better his life: to traffic drugs or to cross the border illegally into the United States. From Sinaloa, Mexico to the streets of South Central and East L.A., Al Otro Lado explores the world of drug smuggling, illegal immigration and the corrido music that chronicles it all.&#8221;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.altamurafilms.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.altamurafilms.com/</a>\n</p><p/></div>", 
