        "author": "Melissa Loyola", 
        "content": "<div><p>Hey Everyone</p>\n<p>Currently I live off-campus with two Brown students, and living with them has allowed me to notice more differences between our academic calendars.</p>\n<p>I say this because today is President&#8217;s Day, and brown students have been able to appreciate the long weekend after a week of midterm finals. My roommates are at home for the holiday, while my classmates are starting the new semester and busying themselves with work. </p>\n<p>I just wanted to open up a discussion concerning the increase of vacation time in our school year? Such as longer breaks and more three-day weekends during lesser holidays. If it were a possibility, I would have minded having a longer school year if that would allow me to have more rest time. I could have definitely appreciated a long weekend during the period before thanksgiving.\n</p><p/></div>", 
