        "author": "Christine Tan", 
        "content": "<div><p>Hello Liz,<br/>\n I would like to request a thread on the behalf of graduating students (or maybe, just me). In the last tuition bill, I noticed we had a $260 graduation fee.</p>\n<p>$260?? Really?? For each student? And for what??</p>\n<p>My father has been trying to get in contact with someone in the administration (not sure who) but has not heard back from anyone - and he has contacted them several times. It&#8217;s been over a month now. My brother and sister have gone through college and neither schools (one ivy league and one state university) charged more than $20 for the graduation fee.</p>\n<p>My thread would like to ask where and what the money is going towards, how RISD charges many &#8220;fees&#8221; (including, and not limited to, department fees) and what is the breakdown of these fees. Specifically for graduation, the only things I know that the money is for are the caps and gowns; other than that, I speculate it is for the catering afterwards, tents, speakers, and the reservation of a PARKING LOT (and from what I have heard, a lot/building that RISD owns?) for the ceremony.</p>\n<p>It concerns me that after being here for almost 5 years, we are still being asked to pay a lot extra to finish. I would like to know if any other students feel the same way and if we could receive some answers.</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n<p>Christine\n</p><p/></div>", 
