        "author": "Damion Vania", 
        "content": "<div><p>Hi Liz,<br/>\nIf appropriate, I&#8217;d like to post a project the Division of Student Life is initiating. Thanks.<br/>\nDamion Vania</p>\n<p>The impact one person can make.<br/>\nYou are invited to anonymously contribute to the Impact of One Project as part of the Nelson Mandela Initiative.  This is an opportunity to recognize a member of the RISD community for the positive impact they have had on you.  This can be from or to students, staff and faculty.<br/>\n1.\tFirst you grab a post card from one of the ten pick up and drop off spots: Office of Student Life, Office of Residents Life, Office of Student Development and Counseling, Health Office, Office of Multicultural Affairs, The Met, Portfolio Caf&#233;, Office of Career Services, CIT, and the Mailroom.<br/>\n2.\tCreate an expression of appreciation on the back (words or images) and fill in the blank of whom you would like to recognize.<br/>\n3.\tDrop off the card back in one of the spots.  The person you are recognizing will receive a button and an explanation of why they got the button.  The last day to submit is Thursday, April 16.  The cards will be on view at the RISD store from April 20 to 25.  After April 25, the cards will be sent to those the cards were made for.<br/>\n Help us to recognize and celebrate not just individuals, but the sense of community we have here at RISD.  Please spread this idea around.\n</p><p/></div>", 
