        "author": "Sara Kudra", 
        "content": "<div><p>It&#8217;s Earth Day!</p>\n<p>To celebrate the occasion the 2nd Life Center is launching the newly revised <a href=\"http://docs.google.com/a/g.risd.edu/Doc?id=ddtqzrhz_0nnhchbvp\" rel=\"nofollow\">Greenlist.</a> This document was originally created by the Green Club, the predecessor to Respond/Design as a guide to ecological resources for the RISD community. </p>\n<p>Since then John has started <a href=\"https://one.risd.edu/index.php/green-risd/\" rel=\"nofollow\">one.risd</a> and this blog, which both have included similar lists of classes and alumni doing ecological work. With the Greenlist we aim to keep this line of inquiry open, and ultimately publish another edition of the list to be distributed across campus as a tangible reference guide. </p>\n<p>This <a href=\"http://docs.google.com/a/g.risd.edu/Doc?id=ddtqzrhz_0nnhchbvp\" rel=\"nofollow\">document</a> is fully open and available to edit by anyone at RISD. Please contribute any knowledge you have to this list, of your own department and work, or the great local business where you just bought recycled paper. Or add it to this thread and we will put it in there for you!</p>\n<p>Thanks!<br/>\nSara</p>\n<p><a>2nd Life Center</a>\n</p><p/></div>", 
